{{Notability|date=September 2011}} {{Infobox software | name = LibreOffice Writer | logo = [[File:LibreOffice 3.3.1 Writer Icon.png|52px]] | screenshot = [[Image:libreoffice writer .png|300px]] | caption = LibreOffice Writer 3 running on [[Ubuntu (operating system)|Ubuntu]] | collapsible = | developer = The Document Foundation | status = Active | latest release version = 3.4.2 | latest release date = {{Release date and age|2011|08|01|df=yes}} | operating system = [[Cross-platform]] | genre = [[Word processor]] | license = [[GNU Lesser General Public Licence|GNU LGPLv3]]<ref name="Lic">{{Cite web|url =http://www.libreoffice.org/download/license/|title = GNU LGPL License|accessdate = 21 June 2011|last = [[The Document Foundation]]|authorlink = |year = undated}}</ref> | website = [http://www.libreoffice.org/features/writer/ www.Libreoffice.org]| }} '''LibreOffice Writer''' is the [[open-source]] [[word processor]] component of the [[LibreOffice]] [[Software package (installation)|software package]] and is a [[Fork (software development)|fork]] of [[OpenOffice.org Writer]]. Writer is a word processor similar to [[Microsoft Word]] and Corel's [[WordPerfect]], with some of their features.
As with the entire LibreOffice suite, Writer can be used across a variety of platforms, including [[Microsoft Windows]], [[Linux]], [[FreeBSD]] and [[Solaris Operating System|Solaris]].
== Features == Writer is capable of opening and saving documents in a number of formats, including the OASIS [[OpenDocument|Open Document Format 1.1]] (its default format), [[Microsoft Word]]'s [[.DOC|DOC]], [[DOCX]], [[Rich Text Format|RTF]] and [[XHTML]].<ref name="WriterHome">{{Cite web|url = http://www.libreoffice.org/features/writer/|title = Writer, a Word Processor for Every Kind of Document|accessdate = 15 June 2011|last = [[The Document Foundation]]|authorlink = |year = undated}}</ref>
Writer provides a number of features, such as the inclusion of a [[word completion]] mechanism for predictive writing and the ability to export to [[PDF]] format.<ref name="WriterHome" />
Features include:<ref name="Intro">{{Cite web|url = http://wiki.documentfoundation.org/cgi_img_auth.php/e/e3/0201WG3-IntroducingWriter.pdf|title = Chapter 1 - Introducing Writer |accessdate = 15 June 2011|last = [[The Document Foundation]]|authorlink = |year = 2011}}</ref>: * Templates and styles *A grammar checker is included by default since release 3.3<ref name="Grammar">{{Cite web|url = http://help.libreoffice.org/Writer/Checking_Spelling_and_Grammar |title = Checking Spelling and Grammar|accessdate = 15 June 2011|last = [[The Document Foundation]]|authorlink = |year = 2011}}</ref> *Support for autofilter per sheet: It is now possible to set autofilter per sheet without manually creating named database ranges prior to setting autofilter<ref name="Features34">{{Cite web|url = http://www.libreoffice.org/download/3-4-new-features-and-fixes/ |title = 3.4 New Features and Fixes|accessdate = 15 June 2011|last = [[The Document Foundation]]|authorlink = |year = undated}}</ref> * Page-layout methods, including frames, columns, and tables * Embedding or linking of graphics, spreadsheets, and other objects * Built-in drawing tools *Java text rendering replaced by native text rendering which greatly improves readability<ref name="Features34" /><ref name="Honline">{{Cite news|url = http://www.h-online.com/open/news/item/LibreOffice-3-4-0-arrives-for-power-users-and-early-adopters-1254892.html|title = LibreOffice 3.4.0 arrives for power users and early adopters|accessdate = 15 June 2011|last = djwm|authorlink = |year = 2011|month = June| work = H On-line}}</ref> *The preexisting Java dialogs have been replaced with simpler native dialog boxes.<ref name="Proffitt07Feb11">{{Cite news|url = http://www.linux.com/learn/tutorials/403466:review-hands-on-libreoffice-33|title = Review: Hands on LibreOffice 3.3|accessdate = 15 June 2011|last = Proffitt|first = Brian|authorlink = |year = 2011|month = June| work = Linux.com}}</ref> *Support Color and line styles for the columns and footnote separator lines. This is improving the compatibility of LibreOffice with ODF<ref name="Features34" /> * Master documentsâto group a collection of documents into a single document * Change tracking during revisions * The ability to import and edit [[PDF]] files as of version 3.4<ref name="Linton01Feb11">{{Cite news|url = http://www.linuxjournal.com/content/libreoffice-33-release-brings-new-features|title = The New Features in LibreOffice 3.3|accessdate = 15 June 2011|last = Linton|first = Susan|authorlink = |year = 2011|month = June| work = Linux Journal}}</ref> *Significantly improved file compatibility when dealing with Microsoft Word as compared to openoffice<ref name="Proffitt07Feb11" /> * Database integration, including a bibliography database * Export to PDF, including bookmarks * MailMerge<ref name="MailMerge">{{Cite web|url = http://wiki.documentfoundation.org/cgi_img_auth.php/0/05/0211WG3-UsingMailMerge.pdf|title = Chapter 11 - Using Mail Merge Form letters, mailing labels, and envelopes |accessdate = 15 June 2011|last = [[The Document Foundation]]|authorlink = |year = 2011}}</ref> * Equation editor ([[LibreOffice Math]])<ref name="Math">{{Cite web|url = http://wiki.documentfoundation.org/cgi_img_auth.php/9/96/0109GS3-GettingStartedWithMath.pdf|title = Chapter 9 - Getting Started with Math LibreOffice's Equation Editor |accessdate = 15 June 2011|last = [[The Document Foundation]]|authorlink = |year = 2011}}</ref> * Scriptable and Remote Controllable via the [[Universal Network Objects|UNO API]] * Indexing * AutoCorrect * AutoComplete * Selection of non-consecutive items in Add Mode.<ref>{{Cite web|url =http://www.libreoffice.org/get-help/documentation/|title = LibreOffice Writer}}</ref>
